  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> rolls initiative with advantage. </p><p><span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> starts with a number of villainous actions equal to one less than it's villainous multiplier. If a hit point pool is depleted, <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> also loses one villainous action. <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> may use a villainous action after any other creature takes a turn. If <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span> does so, it regains its reaction. A villainous action is a complete turn. They have an action, bonus action and may move up to their full speed. The villainous actions refresh at the start of <span style=\"font-family:'Open Sans', sans-serif\">{creature}</span>'s turn and any remaining actions from the previous turn are lost.</p>",
